{"id": "EUVD-2025-201874", "enisaUuid": "fe9069e8-ef74-3f37-a682-431cd25c8226", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\nsmb: client: fix potential UAF in smb2_close_cached_fid()\n\nfind_or_create_cached_dir() could grab a new reference after kref_put()\nhad seen the refcount drop to zero but before cfid_list_lock is acquired\nin smb2_close_cached_fid(), leading to use-after-free.\n\nSwitch to kref_put_lock() so cfid_release() is called with\ncfid_list_lock held, closing that gap.", "datePublished": "2025-12-09T18:30:35", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-09T18:30:35", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/cb52d9c86d70298de0ab7c7953653898cbc0efd6", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/065bd62412271a2d734810dd50336cae88c54427", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/bdb596ceb4b7c3f28786a33840263728217fbcf5", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/734e99623c5b65bf2c03e35978a0b980ebc3c2f8", "https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2025-40328"], "aliases": ["CVE-2025-40328"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "00b98dc7-cc60-3efd-9fa8-1412ae1fdafb", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ebe98f1447bbccf8228335c62d86af02a0ed23f7 <bdb596ceb4b7c3f28786a33840263728217fbcf5"}, {"id": "29ed266e-d627-3d78-af3f-55aebb16615b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.12.58"}, {"id": "54ec3ae6-d437-365f-9332-77a6d0a87f8a", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.18"}, {"id": "6aacd666-f723-35b2-b889-0e5f9a12a64d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "6.1"}, {"id": "710c423f-ff65-3f3e-9c9b-2a18d824f0e3", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "ebe98f1447bbccf8228335c62d86af02a0ed23f7 <734e99623c5b65bf2c03e35978a0b980ebc3c2f8"}, {"id": "80809c03-8192-3c45-b05d-dd3cb8ee1f95", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.6.117"}, {"id": "bfd75c81-058b-3d2f-8a20-9c36e626e028", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch